      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The separation happens because the milk protein in the egg yolk stops acting as the glue that keeps the butter fat suspended when the emulsion gets too hot or the butter cooks into an oil. Essentially, you've melted the very foundation of the sauce, causing the fats to rush away from the liquid phase. To re-emulsify it, you need to gently recombine these components from a lukewarm temperature, but fixing it is rarely as simple as letting it set.",
